    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AnalyzerFactory
    A factory class for creating a list of LogAnalyzer objects based on the analysis types specified in the configuration.
    AnomalyDetector
    AnomalyDetector identifies bursts of log entries based on configured severity levels within a given time window.
    ConfigManager
    ConfigManager is responsible for loading and providing access to the configuration settings from a properties file.
    Controller
    The main controller responsible for coordinating the log analysis process.
    LevelCounter
    LevelCounter is responsible for counting the occurrences of different log levels (e.g.
    LogAnalyzer
    An interface for analyzing log entries.
    LogEntry
    Represents a single log entry parsed from a log file.
    LogFileProcessor
    Responsible for processing a single log file and delegating each line to the appropriate LogAnalyzer implementations.
    Main
    Entry point of the log analysis application.
    ReportBuilder
    Utility class responsible for generating and saving a JSON report based on the results of the log analysis.
    SourceCounter
    SourceCounter is responsible for counting how many times each source appears in the log entries.
